                     <interp inst="t18300527-139-person1182" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I received these shoes from Mr. Golding's man; the prisoner gave himself up quietly.</p>
               <p>MR. GOLDING. I was in my parlour, and there is a glass window there, but on the Friday before he attempted to take a pair - then he came a second time, and I said it would not be the last time; I am certain of him - I never lost sight of him.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. It is false; they laid hold of me like a dog, and almost choaked me.</p>
